
[1]commodious

   COMMODIOUS, a. Convenient; suitable; fit; proper; adapted to its use or
   purpose, or to wants and necessities; as a commodious house or room.

   The haven was not commodious to winter in. Acts 27:12.

   It is followed by for before a noun; as a place commodious for a camp.
